### 3. Webhooks Persistence (In-Memory Only) ✅ IMPLEMENTED

**Status:** ~~In-memory GenServer~~ → Full Ecto persistence + Oban job delivery (2026-02-18)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [20260217000005_create_webhook_tables.exs](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/priv/repo/migrations/20260217000005_create_webhook_tables.exs) | NEW: Migration creates `webhook_endpoints` (url, secret, events, active, metadata, failure_count) and `webhook_deliveries` (event, payload, status, attempts, response tracking) tables with indexes |
| [endpoint.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/webhooks/endpoint.ex) | NEW: Ecto schema for webhook endpoints with changeset validation, `sanitize/1` masks secret. `has_many :deliveries`. |
| [delivery.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/webhooks/delivery.ex) | NEW: Ecto schema for delivery records tracking event, payload, status (pending/sending/success/failed), attempts, response code/body, retry scheduling |
| [webhook_delivery_worker.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/workers/webhook_delivery_worker.ex) | NEW: Oban worker (`queue: :webhooks`) — fetches delivery+endpoint from DB, HTTP POSTs via `CGraph.Finch` with HMAC-SHA256 signature, updates delivery status, schedules retries with exponential backoff (1s/5s/30s/2m/10m) |
| [webhooks.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/webhooks.ex) | REWRITE: Converted from 971-line GenServer with in-memory state to ~400-line plain Ecto context module. All CRUD via `Repo`. `dispatch/3` queries active endpoints, creates Delivery records, enqueues Oban jobs. Removed all `handle_call/cast/info`, `process_pending_queue`, `schedule_*` functions. |

---

### 4. Voice/Video Channels (Schema Only, No Backend) ✅ IMPLEMENTED

**Status:** ~~Schema only~~ → Call history persistence + TURN/SFU config wiring (2026-02-18)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| [call_history.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/webrtc/call_history.ex) | NEW: Ecto schema for persisted call history — room_id, type (audio/video/screen_share), creator_id, group_id, participant_ids array, duration_seconds, max_participants, started_at/ended_at |
| [20260217000005_create_webhook_tables.exs](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/priv/repo/migrations/20260217000005_create_webhook_tables.exs) | Includes `call_history` table creation with indexes on creator_id, group_id, started_at |
| [webrtc.ex](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/lib/cgraph/webrtc/webrtc.ex) | Added `persist_call_history/2` called in both `end_room` and `leave_room` (last participant) handlers. Records room_id, type, creator_id, group_id, participant_ids, max_participants, started_at, ended_at, duration_seconds. Added `list_call_history/2` and `get_call/1` public query functions. |
| [runtime.exs](file:///CGraph/apps/backend/config/runtime.exs) | TURN server config now reads from `WEBRTC_TURN_URL`, `WEBRTC_TURN_USERNAME`, `WEBRTC_TURN_CREDENTIAL` env vars. Added `WEBRTC_SFU_ENABLED` and `WEBRTC_SFU_URL` configuration. |

